 7-7 7"}]}]]}],["$","a",null,{"href":"#services","className":"btn btn-ghost btn-lg","children":"Services"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"reveal reveal-4","style":{"animationDelay":"0.55s"},"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"reveal reveal-4","style":{"animationDelay":"0.55s"},"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"hero-card","children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"— Coding Accuracy · 30-day view"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"ICD-10 Accuracy"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value green","children":"96%"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"CPT Accuracy"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value green","children":"94%"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"Modifier Accuracy"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value amber","children":"88%"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"Doc–Code Alignment"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value green","children":"97%"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"Coding Denial Rate"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value","children":["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-pill pill-green","children":"2.1% ↓"}]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-row","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-label","children":"Errors Caught Pre-Submit"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-value green","children":"14"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-stats","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-stat","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-num","children":"341"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-label","children":"Claims Reviewed"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-stat","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-num","children":"0"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-label","children":"Unbilled Visits"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"dash-stat","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-num green","children":"$$18.4K"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"dash-stat-label","children":"Revenue Protected"}]]}]]}]]}]}]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block","id":"pain","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"The coding reality every practice knows"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Coding happens under pressure. <em>Accurate coding requires something pressure never allows.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"monologue fade-in","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"","children":"The provider finishes a complex visit, documents quickly between the next patient, and the coder assigns a code based on what the chart says. Or what the chart implies. Or what it usually says for this type of visit."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"","children":"Nobody is being careless. The coder is experienced. The provider documented. But the documentation was rushed, the modifier was not specified, and the diagnosis did not quite align with the procedure as the payer reads it. The claim goes out. Three weeks later, it comes back denied."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"highlight","children":"\"You already know the pressure of submitting claims while hoping the documentation is strong enough to support them. That hope is not a revenue strategy.\""}],["$","p","3",{"className":"","children":"Coding accuracy is not just a billing problem. It is a documentation problem, a workflow problem, and a communication problem between the clinical side and the billing side of your practice. When those two sides are not aligned — the codes that go out do not always match the care that was delivered."}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--warm","id":"pain-details","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"Where the problem lives"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The specific gaps <em>behind the surface.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-ledger fade-in","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Codes are selected under schedule pressure"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Coders work at the pace the schedule demands. When there is no time to verify that the documentation fully supports the selected code level, the code gets assigned and the claim moves forward — with whatever risk that creates."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Documentation does not always support the billed service"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The provider performed the service. But the chart entry does not document it completely enough to satisfy the payer's review criteria. The code is technically correct. The documentation just does not prove it — and payers make decisions based on what they can see, not what the provider intended."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Modifier errors create silent revenue loss"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"One missing modifier. One incorrect modifier. One modifier that was required for this specific payer but not flagged in the workflow. The claim gets reduced, denied, or bundled — and without a systematic review, the error repeats on every similar claim going forward."}]]}]]}],["$","div","04",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Payer coding rules change and nobody tracks them"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Payers update their coding requirements regularly. LCD updates, CPT revisions, NCCI edits, payer-specific bundling rules. When those changes are not captured and reflected in the billing workflow, claims start failing for reasons the team did not see coming."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Coding errors repeat across providers and over time"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When a coder makes a systematic error — the same wrong code for the same procedure type — that error multiplies across every similar claim until someone catches it. Without a regular coding review, those patterns go unnoticed for months."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Incorrect coding creates compliance exposure"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Upcoding, undercoding, and unbundling are not just billing errors. They are compliance risks. Without a layer of review that catches these patterns before they become habits, the practice accumulates exposure it does not know is building."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],"$undefined",["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--ink","id":"solution","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"The solution"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display display--light","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Accurate coding before the claim goes out. <em>Not a correction after it comes back denied.</em>"}}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Hired Billing Support embeds coding support directly into your billing workflow — reviewing codes, verifying documentation alignment, flagging modifier issues, and ensuring that what goes out matches both the care delivered and the payer's requirements."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"two-col fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-list","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Coding review before submission"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"We review codes against documentation before claims go out — not after denials arrive. ICD-10 accuracy, CPT selection, modifier application, and diagnosis-procedure linkage reviewed on every claim in scope."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Documentation-to-code alignment"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"We review whether the clinical documentation supports the billed service level. When it does not, we flag the gap before submission — not after a payer rejects the claim for insufficient documentation."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Payer-specific rule application"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Different payers have different coding requirements. We apply those rules at the claim level so your coding reflects what each payer actually requires, not just what is generally correct."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"process-list","children":[["$","div","04",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Error pattern identification and feedback"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When a coding error repeats across claims or providers, we document the pattern, identify the root cause, and communicate the finding to your coding team or billing manager so it stops recurring."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Specialty-specific coding support"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Coding for surgical procedures, E/M visits, mental health services, and specialty care requires specific knowledge. We provide coding support aligned to your specialty and payer mix."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Denial root cause — coding category"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When a claim is denied for a coding reason, we trace the exact error, correct the claim, and document the root cause so the same denial does not repeat."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block","id":"services","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"Coding services included"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Every layer of coding accuracy. <em>Reviewed before the claim leaves your system.</em>"}}],["$","p",null,{"children":"We do not specialize in one piece of the coding puzzle. We own the full workflow so nothing falls in the gap between departments or responsibilities."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"services-grid fade-in","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"service-item","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"service-num","children":"01"}],["$","h4",null,{"children":"ICD-10-CM Coding Review"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Diagnosis code a